Connect to SQL Server - 2 types
       1. Using MSTSC (Remote Desktop Connection)/RDP -> Username
       2. IP Address
  -> it asks for Credentials -> username & password
  -> you will connect to server
  -> open search & type SSMS (Microsoft SQL Server Management studio) -> open it
           -> Servertype: Database engine
           -> Server Name: Hari\JettiExpress
           -> Authentication: Windows Authentication
                  username: xxxxxxx
                  password: xxxxxxx
                -> click on connect
                
any issues -> connect to a particular server -> fix the issues 

When we Connect it:
  Server name (Jetti Express) & under it we can see :
     * Database (Complete data)
          System database
          Andhra (user database)
          Telengana (user database)
     * Security
          Logins
          server roles
          credentials
     * Server objects
          backup devices
          linked devices
          triggers
     * Replication
          local subscription
     * Management
          policy management
          extended events
          SQL server logs
     * SQL Server agent
     
     SQL Servers            Versions
  MS SQL Server 2019       15.0.426.1
  MS SQL Server 2017         14
  MS SQL Server 2016         13
  MS SQL Server 2014         12
  MS SQL Server 2012         11
  MS SQL Server 2008         10
  MS SQL Server 2005          9

issues, updates & bugs fix by the microsoft & releases in form of Cummulative Updates (CU's) -> Service packs(sp1, sp2, sp3)

To Find Versions:
  Click -> New Query
  Write -> SELECT @@VERSION
  Click -> Execute 
 you can see the version of the SQL server.
  


  
  
